Allow parse/unparse callbacks to stop execution.

Add a mechanism to allow parse/unparse callbacks to exit early from their
respective parse loops(MPACK_THROW) macro. This is useful to allow language
bindings to throw exceptions.

Merge PR #20 'Human-readable tostring(mpack.NIL)'

[lua] Add mpack.NIL string representation

Assign a metatable to the mpack.NIL userdata object, containing
a custom __tostring definition.
https://www.lua.org/pil/29.1.html
http://lua-users.org/lists/lua-l/2006-08/msg00245.html

In lua, mpack.NIL is different than Lua nil. But that is confusing
for users who might expect msgpack NIL to deserialize to Lua nil.
Human-readable string representation helps avoid that confusion.

Björn Linse:
> In lua nil may mean undefined, it is used for missing args,
> nonexistent globals, etc., so there are ambiguities.
> Example: If msgpack dict has NIL values, it cannot be represented in
> lua, because in lua nil means the key is missing, and thus can't be
> a dict value.

References https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/5694

Signed-off-by: James McCoy <jamessan@jamessan.com>

Add "exiting" flag to parser struct

This flag is used to normalize how leaf `mpack_node_t` instances are treated by
the `mpack_unparse_tok` function. With this change, `mpack_unparse_tok` will
return after `enter_cb` is invoked(previously this only happened on non-leaf
nodes).

This was done mainly to give `mpack_unparse` a chance to invoke `mpack_write`
before `exit_cb` is invoked on leaf nodes, which is necessary in cases where the
user's `exit_cb` frees some buffer read by `mpack_write`.

Invoke gdb through libtool `--mode=execute`

Now that `-rpath` is passed to libtool, gdb can't be invoked directly on the
test program because it is a wrapper script.
